The paper proposes an unsupervised learning method using convolutional neural networks for 3D medical image registration. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm that achieves state-of-the-art performance, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
